    {
      "id": "users-document-view",
      "type": "document-view",
      "label": "Document View",
      "root": true,
      "position": {
        "x": 560,
        "y": 820
      },
      "width": 440,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Hosted Users",
        "localTitle": "Hosted Users",
        "publishedTitle": "Hosted Users",
        "purpose": "Compose the hosted users task graph into one readable document surface.",
        "titleSourceNodeId": "users-title",
        "audience": "Reader",
        "status": "active",
        "viewRole": "document",
        "viewKind": "display",
        "exposedAuthority": "consume-view",
        "runtimeExposed": false,
        "partNodeIds": [
          "users-title",
          "landing-page-seriousness-summary",
          "landing-seriousness-overview",
          "landing-seriousness-entry",
          "landing-seriousness-identity",
          "landing-seriousness-hierarchy",
          "landing-seriousness-signals",
          "landing-seriousness-conversion",
          "landing-seriousness-sequence",
          "landing-seriousness-questions",
          "landing-seriousness-output",
          "tasks-landing-page-seriousness-task-node-task",
          "tasks-landing-page-seriousness-task-node-question"
        ],
        "documentOrder": [
          "users-title",
          "landing-page-seriousness-summary",
          "landing-seriousness-overview",
          "landing-seriousness-entry",
          "landing-seriousness-identity",
          "landing-seriousness-hierarchy",
          "landing-seriousness-signals",
          "landing-seriousness-conversion",
          "landing-seriousness-sequence",
          "landing-seriousness-questions",
          "landing-seriousness-output",
          "tasks-landing-page-seriousness-task-node-task",
          "tasks-landing-page-seriousness-task-node-question"
        ],
        "documentHtml": "<section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;box-sizing:border-box;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,252,245,0.99), rgba(255,248,235,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(146,64,14,0.16);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(180,83,9,0.10);gap:14px;\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;min-width:0;\"><div style=\"font:700 11px/1.2 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#b45309;\">Title</div><div style=\"font:700 28px/1.12 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;word-break:break-word;\">Hosted Users</div></div><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-end;gap:6px;flex-shrink:0;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(180,83,9,0.1);color:#92400e;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.04em;\">headline</span><span style=\"font:600 10px/1.2 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#9a3412;opacity:0.72;\">active</span></div></div><div style=\"height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(245,158,11,0.45), rgba(245,158,11,0));\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.65 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#4b5563;\">Define the durable user model for Twilite: canonical identity, hosted workspace ownership, and explicit work/public/private repo mappings.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Implement hosted users and durable user data</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(219,39,119,0.14);color:#9d174d;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Summary</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #db2777, #f472b6);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\"><strong>Goal:</strong> Implement hosted users and durable user data<br><br><strong>Tasks In Scope</strong><br>1. Define the implementation path<br><br><strong>Open Questions</strong><br>1. What remains unresolved about users?</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">0/1 tasks complete • 0/1 questions answered</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"users-infrastructure\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Users Infrastructure</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Twilite now has meaningful user data in more than one place, so pretending there is no user model is no longer viable.<br><br>This task graph defines the work needed to implement hosted users, durable server-side user data, and explicit mappings between each user&#39;s `work/`, `public/`, and `private/` folders and their corresponding repos.<br><br>Direction: take the most flexible route, since hosted auth and persistence come with the web deployment anyway.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"identity-boundary\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Identity Boundary</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Twilite needs a canonical user identity boundary.<br><br>The system should stop relying on browser-local state for important product data and establish a hosted user record that can survive devices, sessions, and repo changes.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"data-ownership\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Data Ownership</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">User-critical state should move into durable hosted storage.<br><br>Examples:<br>- repo mappings<br>- default save destination<br>- selected GitHub installation<br>- workspace preferences that should follow the user<br><br>`localStorage` can remain a cache and convenience layer, but not the source of truth.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"repo-mapping-model\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Repo Mapping Model</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">A hosted user should own explicit repo mappings for `work`, `public`, and `private`.<br><br>That mapping is the durable contract between Twilite and GitHub, and it should not be inferred from whichever browser tab happened to be open last.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"durable-workspace-state\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Durable Workspace State</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The hosted workspace should own the user&#39;s default save slot, selected provider context, onboarding state, and any repo-linked preferences that need to follow the user across devices.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"auth-strategy\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Auth Strategy</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">GitHub should attach to the Twilite user through provider identities rather than becoming the user record itself.<br><br>That keeps the system flexible enough to add other providers later without redoing the core data model.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"implementation-sequence\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Implementation Sequence</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Start with the canonical schema, then bind auth, then resolve the workspace on sign-in, then make `work` the default save destination.<br><br>Do not try to migrate every local preference in the first slice.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"questions-to-answer\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Questions To Answer</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Key questions:<br>- What should count as the canonical Twilite user identity?<br>- Which user data should stay local, and which must become server-owned?<br>- How should repo mappings be represented and edited?<br>- How should we migrate today&#39;s browser-local state without breaking people?</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"product-export-goal\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Product Export Goal</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Once this is answered, Twilite should have a real user infrastructure foundation strong enough to support hosted setup flows, persistent repo mappings, and trustworthy multi-device use without losing the graph-native model.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Define the implementation path</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(16,185,129,0.16);color:#047857;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Task</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #10b981, #34d399);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Decide the concrete implementation path for hosted users, canonical user records, repo mappings, and default save behavior, then break that into shippable tasks across auth, persistence, migration, and UX.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Status: todo • Priority: high • Owner: Michael • Estimate: 2h</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">What remains unresolved about users?</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(168,85,247,0.14);color:#7c3aed;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Open Question</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #a855f7, #c084fc);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Capture the highest-value unresolved question still blocking or sharpening the hosted users implementation, especially around identity choice, migration, and how much browser-local state should remain.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Status: open • Owner: Michael</div></div></section>",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "document-view",
